    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="698"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Damages stated at Bible House as not excessive—for Harpoot, $87, 985; for Marash,
                    $10,560. Letters from Gates, Harpoot, charge that orders which controlled
                    movements of attacking party, which resulted in burning, issued from Mustapha
                    Pasha, commander in chief of army division. Telegram from Marash dated 16th
                    reports all safe and protected. Can communicate by mail and telegraph with
                    Marash. Missionaries will not express desire to leave unless instructed.</p>
                <p>* * * * * * *</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
